Q1:Difference between demon set and stateful set with example use case?
Ans: DS ensures that every node runs exact one instance of pod .it is used in case when workloads is node-scoped not an application-scoped
ex monitoring system(prometheus,DataDog) whereas stateful set is used for stateful Application that require stable pod identity ,persitent
volumes ,ordered deployments/updates
Q2: What are sidear containers?
Ans: These are helping containers that run alongside every containers inside pod , (usually there is one to one mapping suggested btw pod 
and container but in some cases these sidecars containers run along with application inside pod).
Q3: What is Blue/green deployment?
A3: This is rollback strategy .
We created two environment in both the environment application is running. but user is accessing only one environment.
Blue-current running environment
Green-Idle environment
We are switching the traffic to green environment if rollback requires by changing matchlabels in service definitons.
It is costly as we require more resources to run identical two environments

ex Databases(mongo,mysql),Distributed system
